**Research findings:**
- Python SDK uses `extra_headers`, `extra_query`, `extra_body`, `timeout` on every method + `with_options()` / `copy()` on client
- In Rust, `client.with_options(opts).chat().completions().create(req)` covers all 40+ resource methods without modifying each one — `reqwest::Client` is Arc-cloned cheaply
- `ClientConfig` needs `default_headers` and `default_query` to match Python SDK constructor
- `extra_body` requires JSON merge at the `request()` level — internal only, doesn't pollute public types
- No deploy infrastructure found — no deploy phase needed
